gomodel:SYNGO_5158  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: Figure 8: Electron microscopic-level immunostaining in area 46 of monkey brain showed RGS14 was exclusively localized to the postsynapse.. Experimental description: monkey species not mentioned in the paper, opted to annotate against Rhesus Macaque.\n\nantibody;\n\"The carboxyl-terminal peptide of human RGS12 (GenBank accession no. AY987042), ARDPRLSKREES, and the N-terminal peptide of human RGS14 (GenBank accession no. AY987041), RKKPKLKPGKS, corresponding to residues 494-505 and 55-65, respectively, were synthesized.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date          "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_5158" ;
